  <discussion>Although I have seen no records from Maine, Xyris torta is to be expected there.</discussion>
  <discussion>Xyris torta is the widest-ranging of all North American xyrids and the most expressive ecologically; thus it is not surprising that it varies so much morphologically. It is much ofthen confused in older nomenclature literature with X. caroliniana. Xyris torta is the type species for the genus.</discussion>
